An agreement that one’s heir should succeed one as partner (except in societas vectigalis) was void: ‘adeo morte socii solvitur societas, ut nec ab initio pacisci possimus ut heres etiam succedat societati' Dig. 17. 2. 59. pr„ ib. 35 ; but the heir, though not a partner, was bound to complete all business commenced by the deceased, being herein answerable for culpa lata only, Dig. ib. 35. 36. 40.
